other_tests.findings: Biliary stent was placed and cytology brushings were obtained (which were negative for malignancy).

The gallbladder is distended with shadowing stones and sludge along with a 6 mm obstructing stone at the gallbladder neck/cystic duct; no pericholecystic fluid or gallbladder wall edema is present. Common bile duct stent shows greater dilatation of the proximal common bile duct, measuring 10 mm.
other_tests.changes_over_time: Recent ultrasound findings better characterized previously demonstrated hemangiomas, and greater dilatation of the common bile duct has been noted.
